div.bibl: Svenska Tribunen, Feb. 25, 1880. GEORGE WASHINGTON BIRTHDAY PARTY.

body.p: Freja Society celebrated the birthday of George Washington on February 22nd with a well arranged supper in its hall on Chicago Ave. The food served by Rudolf Sylvan was excellent. The spiritual meal consisted of songs and speeches. The toast for Washington was proposed by P.S.Sundelius. Other speakers were Lange and Nyquist. ....
